1
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:13,360
(Previously)
Do I…

2
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:14,800
have cancer, Doctor?

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,320
Fortunately, it's still treatable.

4
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:19,200
You need to get better first, okay?

5
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:22,680
I'll take you everywhere you want to go.

6
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,000
I feel like...

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,240
I can touch other people again.

8
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:27,600
Sailom...

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:29,400
Will you be my boyfriend?

10
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,680
Is it going to be a burden

11
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,400
to be with a broken man like me?

12
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,200
We'll have to find out.

13
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:48,000
"Love Like a Bike"
(Episode 7)

14
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,560
You look pretty cheerful today.

15
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,640
The boss sent me for the interest.

16
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,280
Hand it over.

17
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,320
Here's your "interest."

18
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,840
DINDIN!!

19
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:11,040
Dindin!

20
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,720
Don't waste your energy running.

21
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,320
Just pay up!

22
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,640
What the hell? I already paid you!

23
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,720
3,000 wasn't enough!

24
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,600
You owe me a million!

25
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,840
A million?
It was only five hundred thousand.

26
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,880
Interest piles up when you miss payments.

27
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,480
That's just business.

28
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:44,000
You're just preying on the poor.

29
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:47,560
I didn't force you to borrow a dime.

30
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:50,200
You all came to me on your own.

31
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,760
Stop yapping

32
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:53,640
and pay the interest!

33
00:02:54,189 --> 00:02:56,836
I won't pay. Even if I have it,
I won't give you a dime.

34
00:02:57,056 --> 00:02:58,356
You said you won't pay, huh?

35
00:03:01,564 --> 00:03:02,570
Not even a dime?

36
00:03:03,397 --> 00:03:04,650
Not paying at all, right?

37
00:03:12,547 --> 00:03:14,194
If you can't get me
that damn money,

38
00:03:18,878 --> 00:03:21,204
then you can pay
with something else.

39
00:03:22,057 --> 00:03:23,637
What are you doing?

40
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,294
It pays a good price.

41
00:03:28,264 --> 00:03:29,330
Just pay with...

42
00:03:37,499 --> 00:03:38,473
This is none of your business.

43
00:03:39,316 --> 00:03:41,110
Are you trying to play hero?

44
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,040
Who were those guys?

45
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:35,480
My loan sharks' goons.

46
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,680
You shouldn't have gotten involved.

47
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,280
Your business is my business too.

48
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,600
I mean...

49
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:54,040
because you're my employee.

50
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,640
Yeah?

51
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:04,680
Why did they beat you up so badly?

52
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,160
They scammed my mom.

53
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,680
At first,

54
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,240
they said no interest.

55
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,880
Then it jumped to 20%.

56
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,880
The principal was only a few hundred
thousand, but it never goes down.

57
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,880
So, you need to do many jobs.

58
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,040
Yes.

59
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:31,320
My mom put this house up as collateral.

60
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:37,960
My grandma's shop had to close down
because those bastards kept harassing us.

61
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:43,080
I promised myself I'd do whatever it takes

62
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:47,360
to save this home.

63
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,320
Dindin,

64
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,800
I believe you can do it.

65
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,120
I'd better go home.

66
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,560
Hey, wait.

67
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,280
I want to…

68
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,280
thank you for earlier...

69
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:24,440
even if you were
being a meddling jerk.

70
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:29,240
Can't you just say
a proper "thank you" for once?

71
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,600
A proper "thank you?"

72
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,640
Fine.

73
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,680
Wait, wait.

74
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,120
Be careful.

75
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:20,960
Be careful of what?

76
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,360
These.

77
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,160
Oh.

78
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,280
Grandma's sleeping.

79
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,880
This is Doctor Nabnueng speaking.

80
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:36,760
Nabnueng, are you doing well?

81
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:38,880
Yes.

82
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:39,960
Look…

83
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:42,960
I'm not calling to pressure you.

84
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:48,360
But I just wanted to know
if you made a decision yet.

85
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,520
Nabnueng! This is me!

86
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,400
Nabnueng,

87
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:06,520
you have a younger sister.

88
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,200
Her name is Nene.

89
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:27,720
She always said she wants
to be a doctor just like you.

90
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:37,840
But I'm here to ask for your help.

91
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,440
Can you please help your sister?

92
00:09:43,506 --> 00:09:44,986
Help her?

93
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,640
What's wrong with her?

94
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,880
She has Aplastic Anemia.

95
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,840
She needs a bone marrow transplant,

96
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,920
but...

97
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:01,560
It has to come from a full sibling.

98
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,360
If anything happens to her...

99
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,120
I can't go on living.

100
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,480
Please, help your sister.

101
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,400
P'Doc and I can touch each other now.

102
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,120
What?! Are you really cured?

103
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:36,440
Cured or not, but the doctor
asked me to be his boyfriend!

104
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,760
- What?! Really?!
- Yay!

105
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,280
- I'm so happy for you.
- Thanks, Lemon.

106
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,080
We have to celebrate this, right?

107
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,720
Maybe later?

108
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:47,520
My boyfriend
just asked me out for dinner.

109
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:51,440
Well, I guess it's just you and me then.

110
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,960
Oh, gimme a sec.

111
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,320
Hello?

112
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:57,440
Are you in front of the house?
Okay, I'm coming down now.

113
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,840
Love you too. Bye-bye.

114
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,640
Were you talking with me?
Soda's taking me out.

115
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,000
I'm off.

116
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,280
See ya.

117
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,960
Sailom, have you eaten yet?
Want to grab something to eat?

118
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,560
Sure, P'Doc! See you soon!

119
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,800
I'm just background noise again.

120
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:27,960
At least I still have my games.

121
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,920
P'Doc!

122
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,840
Is something wrong?

123
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:56,280
Just... a little bit.

124
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:01,440
Take a deep breath.

125
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,520
You're here with me now.

126
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:06,840
If there's anything bothering you,

127
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,960
you can tell me.

128
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,360
I'm just troubled.

129
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,240
My birth mother came back.

130
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,120
What?

131
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,720
Are you...

132
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:26,560
are you okay?

133
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,920
I'm in a difficult position.

134
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,040
She said my sister is sick

135
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:40,480
and needs my help.

136
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,640
How can you help?

137
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,880
A bone marrow transplant.

138
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,600
Will… it be dangerous?

139
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,480
Is it going to be hard for you?

140
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,440
What kind of illness is it?

141
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,320
She has Aplastic Anemia.

142
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,400
She needs a transplant.

143
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:06,480
It has to come from a full
sibling with the same parents.

144
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,400
Are you going to do it?

145
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,760
I haven't decided yet.

146
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:30,040
I always tell my patients
to listen to their own hearts

147
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,720
to find out what they truly want,

148
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,760
so they can solve their issues.

149
00:13:41,513 --> 00:13:43,713
But when it's my turn,

150
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,920
I have no idea what I want,

151
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,280
or what I should do.

152
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:55,560
I don't even know how…

153
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,080
I'm…

154
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:02,960
supposed to feel.

155
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:09,160
The parents who
abandoned me at birth

156
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:13,200
are now asking me to save a sister.

157
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,440
P'Doc.

158
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:35,600
No matter what you decide,

159
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,560
I'm right here with you.

160
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,200
Hey!

161
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,440
I pay you to serve coffee,
not to shake your asses!

162
00:15:26,713 --> 00:15:28,953
Chill out! It's for the shop's page.

163
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,240
To bring in customers!

164
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:33,560
There are so many people watching.

165
00:15:34,306 --> 00:15:38,186
All I see is you
thrusting your crotches! Move it!

166
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:41,360
Come and help me wash dishes.

167
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,600
Old man,

168
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:52,760
try this new recipe.

169
00:15:58,480 --> 00:15:59,560
How is it?

170
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,360
Good.

171
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,720
Another bite?

172
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:08,120
I knew you'd like it.

173
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:09,560
Ooh!

174
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:12,680
Look at you two!

175
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:16,640
Is something going on between you two?

176
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,200
Hiding something?

177
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,520
- Going to take out the trash?
- Yep.

178
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:23,200
Here, let me help you with that.

179
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:33,680
Gimme that.

180
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,160
P'Dindin,

181
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:39,040
I saw you feeding P'Tawan.

182
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,240
Tell me, are you guys dating?

183
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,960
No! We're nothing!

184
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,360
Your voice went high.

185
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,040
We're nothing.

186
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,360
You're suspicious.

187
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:54,760
I'll show you suspicious! Come here!

188
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,280
- Get back inside.
- No! Stop!

189
00:16:57,320 --> 00:17:00,520
You're not suspicious! Help me!

190
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,240
Move the drinks to this spot.

191
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,720
Is it prettier?

192
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:13,440
Let's take a selfie.

193
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,280
Let see.

194
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,400
What?

195
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:29,640
It looks funny, doesn't it?

196
00:17:31,066 --> 00:17:33,026
How is it funny?

197
00:17:37,393 --> 00:17:39,873
Hey, what was that for?

198
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:46,280
Pattaya's sun is strong recently.

199
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:49,400
Oh, yeah. I have this with me.

200
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,760
Wanna try?

201
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,400
Yeah.

202
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:26,320
You'll get better soon, sweetie.

203
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,640
Nabnueng.

204
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,080
Hello.

205
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:44,160
Nabnueng, this is Nene,

206
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,920
your sister I told you about.

207
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,240
Hello.

208
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,840
Hello.

209
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:57,440
You're way more handsome than
in the pictures Mom showed me.

210
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,440
You're very cute yourself.

211
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,480
Thank you.

212
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,640
And...

213
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:07,360
who is this handsome man?

214
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,160
This is P'Sailom.

215
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,040
He's my boyfriend.

216
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:15,400
Nice to meet you.

217
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:22,560
How are you doing?

218
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:28,520
I'm so bored. I want to go outside,

219
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:31,040
but Mom and Dad won't let me.

220
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,960
You're not fully recovered yet.

221
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:38,400
But I'll be better soon, right?

222
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:40,280
Like you guys said?

223
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,480
Yes.

224
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:48,600
When I get better,

225
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,480
you have to take me to the beach.

226
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:54,720
I want to play in the
water and build sandcastles.

227
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:59,160
P'Doctor and P'Sailom,
you have to come with me, okay?

228
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:07,480
Of course.

229
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,960
Yay.

230
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:13,760
Mom, P'Doctor
and P'Sailom will go with me.

231
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:19,560
But you must get treated first.

232
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,240
Yes.

233
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:26,040
Is it hard being a doctor?
I want to be one too.

234
00:20:26,066 --> 00:20:28,626
I want to be cool just like you.

235
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,520
Yes,

236
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:41,160
you can definitely be a doctor.

237
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,720
Water for you.

238
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,880
Nene is really sweet.

239
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,200
Yeah,

240
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,000
she really is.

241
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,760
I've made my decision.

242
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:02,240
I'm going to help her.

243
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,040
I've been thinking to myself,

244
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:14,160
throughout my career,
I've helped so many patients.

245
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:18,720
I've treated them until
they recovered and could move on.

246
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:24,280
If I set aside my personal feelings,

247
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:28,440
there's no reason
why I shouldn't help Nene.

248
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:33,520
I'm so proud of you, P'Doc.

249
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:51,280
Micky, don't you think the café's
been packed every day lately?

250
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,080
Yeah, I think so too.

251
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:57,240
Maybe it's our TikToks
that are bringing them in?

252
00:22:58,120 --> 00:22:59,560
I'm heading out.

253
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:00,680
Yep.

254
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:03,280
P'Dindin! Wait for me!

255
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,920
Open the door for me.

256
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:07,560
Sure. Taking out the trash?

257
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:09,720
- Yep.
- Here, let me help.

258
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:11,680
Okay.

259
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:27,880
I'll take that.

260
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:32,520
Thank you, P'Dindin.

261
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,680
Sure thing. I'm off then.

262
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:37,360
See you tomorrow. Bye-bye.

263
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,480
Bye-bye.

264
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,640
- I'm going.
- See yah.

265
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:46,080
- Bye!
- Bye-bye.

266
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,560
Shut up!

267
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:14,360
Where did Looksoh go?

268
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,040
Have you seen your sister?

269
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:19,200
I just saw her taking out the trash.

270
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,280
Is she back inside yet?

271
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,520
Not yet.

272
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,960
I was washing dishes
in the kitchen and didn't see her.

273
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:27,960
I didn't see her either.

274
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:42,000
She's not picking up.

275
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:45,320
Everyone, please help me find her.

276
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:32,640
If you want to hear a song
you want, just write it down.

277
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,720
If you don't send the money,

278
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:50,040
I'll film myself cutting
this brat's kidney out.

279
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,200
Let me go!!

280
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,520
And don't even call the cops.

281
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:02,560
You know whose pocket they're in.

282
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:10,360
Who the hell are these bastards?

283
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:17,440
They... are my loan shark's goons.

284
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,680
Why the hell did they take Looksoh?!

285
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:25,320
They want me to pay them back...

286
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:29,240
- a million baht.
- A million?!

287
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:31,440
That much?

288
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:36,320
But what did Looksoh ever do to them?

289
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:41,160
They must have known I work here…

290
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,760
so they took her to blackmail me.

291
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:54,320
Auntie Pailin, I'm sorry.

292
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:56,400
I'm so sorry.

293
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,760
Auntie Pailin, I'm sorry.

294
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,320
I'm so sorry.

295
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,160
Please forgive me.

296
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,440
Then I'm to blame too.

297
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:14,120
I stepped in to help Dindin the other day.

298
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:18,240
They're probably getting back at me.

299
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:21,000
It's my fault...

300
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,840
I failed to protect my daughter.

301
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:26,920
Everyone, calm down.

302
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,640
This is not the time for blame.

303
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:34,440
We need to focus on how
to get Looksoh back. And quickly.

304
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:37,400
Dindin.

305
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,280
Yes?

306
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:39,960
Did they send a location?

307
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:44,640
Here.

308
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:48,480
They said we must bring the money…

309
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,280
before 3 AM.

310
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,160
3 AM?

311
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,960
We only have two hours left.

312
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:17,000
This is a hundred thousand in cash.

313
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,280
Yes, Mom.

314
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:21,120
It's all I could find.

315
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:22,800
That's okay, Mom.

316
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,280
I put in three hundred thousand.

317
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:27,160
Tawan added a hundred and fifty.

318
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,840
Plus Mom's hundred thousand

319
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:31,240
and P'Nueng's hundred and fifty.

320
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,880
The total is seven hundred thousand.

321
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,000
Oh, no.

322
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:38,320
We're still three hundred thousand short.

323
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:44,080
It's almost 2 AM. Where are we
going to find the rest in time?

324
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,800
Everyone,

325
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:51,920
another message.

326
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:55,800
Let me go!!

327
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:58,680
Shut up! Or I'll blast your guts out!

328
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:01,920
You have less than an hour left.

329
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,280
If the money isn't here,

330
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:06,080
I'm taking this brat's kidney.

331
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:23,680
Let me go! Kidnapping for ransom
in this day? So backward!

332
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,960
Why don't you talk it out?! How can
you use violence against a kid like this?!

333
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:31,000
How were you even raised?!
I don't want to educate you,

334
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:33,440
but can you act like civilized adults?!

335
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:36,640
I told you guys to shut her up!

336
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,840
What kind of brat talks this much?!
Is there a motor in her mouth?!

337
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,880
It's better than being
a rotten adult like you!!

338
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,240
Hold still!

339
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:49,360
What time is it?

340
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,840
Almost 3 AM, Boss.

341
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:56,080
If they aren't here in ten minutes,

342
00:29:57,280 --> 00:30:00,560
go get the surgical tools ready.

343
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,120
Where's the money?

344
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:32,680
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

345
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:37,920
Slow down. Money first.

346
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:41,280
A fair trade—cash for the kid.

347
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,480
Give it here!

348
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:48,000
You said it's a fair trade.

349
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:52,360
So why should I hand over the cash first?

350
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:54,880
Untie my sister.

351
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:56,840
Bring her to the middle.

352
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,400
I'll walk to you with the money,

353
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:03,520
take my sister,
and you get the cash. Deal?

354
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:06,560
How do I know you're not playing tricks?

355
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:07,880
Look at us.

356
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:09,800
We're unarmed

357
00:31:10,080 --> 00:31:11,560
and outnumbered.

358
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,360
You have the upper hand here.

359
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:18,840
Untie her.

360
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:29,560
Get over here!

361
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:32,120
- P'Nabnueng!
- Hey!! Shut it!

362
00:31:33,360 --> 00:31:37,240
One more word and
I'll shoot your brothers one by one.

363
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:41,160
Let Dindin bring the money here.

364
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:43,080
It doesn't matter who brings the money!

365
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,160
How dare you bargain with me!

366
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,080
Okay, okay.

367
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,280
Put it down!

368
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:04,400
Let the kid go first.

369
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,880
You think you can negotiate?

370
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:18,000
- How could you do that?!
- I gotta make sure

371
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,960
the money is all here.

372
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,880
Take the money, now!

373
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:26,880
Stay still.

374
00:32:32,680 --> 00:32:34,240
Count every single baht!

375
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:45,400
Now we're even.

376
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:01,440
Mom!

377
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:03,280
Looksoh!

378
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:06,160
Are you okay, baby?
Are you hurt anywhere?

379
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:09,440
I'm okay. Everyone came
to save me just in time.

380
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:13,440
Thank god, you're safe now.

381
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,440
Auntie,

382
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:22,640
I'm so sorry for causing all this trouble.

383
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,000
Dindin,

384
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,840
it's okay.

385
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:29,560
Let the past be the past.

386
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:31,520
The problem is solved.

387
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:34,040
Everything is settled.

388
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:43,720
Looksoh,

389
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:46,640
I'm so sorry.

390
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,360
It's okay.

391
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:58,280
Are you okay, P'Doc?

392
00:33:58,280 --> 00:33:59,480
Sailom?

393
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,440
How did you get here?

394
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:11,560
Sky! You okay, man?!

395
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:14,040
I saw the Boss
and the guys heading out to help you!

396
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,600
Yeah, I'm fine.

397
00:34:16,040 --> 00:34:18,000
Good to hear.

398
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:58,840
Does it hurt?

399
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:08,480
Can I hold your hand?

400
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,520
Sure.

401
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:44,440
Can I touch your cheek?

402
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:50,400
Yes.

403
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:25,480
If this is too much for you,

404
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:27,760
I can stop.

405
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,480
No, don't.

406
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,440
Don't stop.

407
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:02,520
I thought I was dreaming about
someone stealing a kiss from me.

408
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:06,240
That wasn't stealing.

409
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:09,600
It's called a "Morning Kiss."

410
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,480
Why?

411
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:14,880
Don't you like it?

412
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:18,920
I do.

413
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:21,320
A lot.

414
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:24,960
What about you?

415
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,600
Like it?

416
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:32,120
I kissed you.

417
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:34,600
Of course I like it.

418
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:39,400
I'm not talking about the kiss.

419
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:44,080
I mean…

420
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:53,200
what we did last night.

421
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:55,160
Like it?

422
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:59,080
- What?
- Answer me.

423
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:01,960
W…

424
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:04,000
what are you talking about?

425
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:07,840
Just answer me.

426
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,960
Did you like it?

427
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,400
Come on.

428
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:16,840
I just…

429
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:22,720
don't want to be the only one enjoying it.

430
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:26,840
I want you to be happy with me.

431
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,640
Now, answer me.

432
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:41,120
I don't remember what we did last night.

433
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:46,200
Do you need a memory refresh then?

434
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:58,160
Remember now?

435
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,480
Stop teasing me.

436
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,520
Just answer me.

437
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:28,800
Nabnueng!

438
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:37,760
I'll go wait for you downstairs.

439
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:50,960
Nabnueng.

440
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:54,200
When did you get back?

441
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:56,240
A while ago.

442
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:59,200
And I've moved back here for good.

443
00:43:01,680 --> 00:43:04,760
I realized I can't live without you.

444
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:14,360
Sailom,

445
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,360
this is Yanin.

446
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:24,920
The ex-girlfriend I told you about.

447
00:43:25,080 --> 00:43:26,200
Yes.

448
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:28,920
Nice to meet you.

449
00:43:29,560 --> 00:43:30,840
Hello.

450
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,480
And Yanin,

451
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:35,560
this is Sailom.

452
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:41,360
My boyfriend.

453
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,840
But you said you'd wait for me.

454
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:51,840
To be honest, I did wait.

455
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:54,280
For a very long time.

456
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:59,120
But you chose to go
and live your own life.

457
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:03,080
I respected your decision.

458
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:07,720
And today...

459
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:11,600
I've made a choice of my own.

460
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:18,080
I hope you can respect mine too.

461
00:44:34,640 --> 00:44:36,360
I should go.

462
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:11,840
Are you ready, P'Doc?

463
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:14,200
I'm ready.

464
00:45:14,560 --> 00:45:16,720
The surgery will take a while.

465
00:45:20,280 --> 00:45:22,240
You'll get through it just fine.

466
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,200
I'll be right here by your side.

467
00:45:25,240 --> 00:45:26,800
Don't be afraid, okay?

468
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,560
Thank you so much, Sailom.

469
00:45:32,320 --> 00:45:34,160
Thank you for staying with me.

470
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,400
Always.

471
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:07,680
(Next Episode) Hurry up and graduate.
Have some pity on the guy over there.

472
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:11,280
You won't go back to being
a pilot because of that kid?

473
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:12,240
You brat!

474
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:14,000
I told you to stay out of my business!

475
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:16,760
If punching me makes
you feel better, go ahead.

476
00:46:16,760 --> 00:46:19,920
He's been staring at his phone
and moping like this for a week now.

477
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:22,160
It's like when he broke up with P'Yanin.

478
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:25,120
Still overthinking? I'm pretty sure
P'Doc is over his ex by now.

479
00:46:25,160 --> 00:46:26,240
I wouldn't be so sure.

480
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:28,480
Some people still
can't let go previous relationships.

481
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:32,080
When you told your ex
that I was your boyfriend,

482
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:33,800
did you really mean it? Or…

